Package jdrasil.algorithms.exact

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BranchAndBoundDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A classical branch and bound algorithm based on QuickBB and its successors.
    BruteForceEliminationOrderDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class computes an optimal tree-decomposition by "brute-forcing" all n!
    CatchAndGlue<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Tree width has nice game theoretic characterisations, one of which is the node-search game played by a set of searchers and a fugitive.
    CopsAndRobber<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    An alternative definition of tree-width is about the cops and robbers game.
    DynamicProgrammingDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class implements exact exponential time (and exponential space) algorithms to compute a tree-decomposition via dynamic programming.
    LimitedGraphSearch<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The tree width of a graph can be characterized from a game theoretic point of view with the graph search game where a team of searchers tries to catch a fugitive, who has unlimited speed.
    SATDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This TreeDecomposer computes a tree-decomposition using the base encoding @see BaseEncoder.java.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CatchAndGlue.Mode
    The algorithm can run in two modes: improving a lower- or an upper-bound.
    DynamicProgrammingDecomposer.Mode
    Three implementation modes of the cited paper.
    SATDecomposer.Encoding
    Different encodings that are supported by this decomposer.
